<section class="section">
  <div class="container">
    <p class="sl">How Our Pricing Works</p>
    <h2>Compressor vs. thermoelectric &mdash; two completely different repair profiles</h2>
    <div class="body-text">
      <p>Wine coolers come in two fundamentally different technologies with very different repair economics. A compressor wine cooler operates like a small refrigerator &mdash; compressor, condenser, evaporator, thermistor. These are durable and fully repairable. A thermoelectric wine cooler uses a Peltier element with no moving parts except a fan &mdash; quiet and vibration-free, but the Peltier element has a limited lifespan and when it fails, repair cost can approach replacement cost on smaller units.</p>
      <p>We diagnose the type and specific failure before quoting anything. The $89 diagnostic fee covers the full assessment. After diagnosis you get two numbers: labor and the specific OEM part. For thermoelectric units with Peltier failure, we give you an honest comparison of repair cost vs. replacement cost before proceeding.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="type-grid">
      <div class="type-card comp">
        <h3>&#10052; Compressor wine coolers</h3>
        <ul class="type-list">
          <li>Operates like a small refrigerator</li>
          <li>More powerful cooling &mdash; handles LA ambient heat better</li>
          <li>Compressor, condenser fan, evaporator, thermistor</li>
          <li>Fully repairable &mdash; same components as standard fridges</li>
          <li>Sub-Zero, True, Perlick, Viking, U-Line</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div class="type-card therm">
        <h3>&#9889; Thermoelectric wine coolers</h3>
        <ul class="type-list">
          <li>Peltier element &mdash; quiet, no vibration</li>
          <li>Struggles in rooms above 75&ndash;80&deg;F (common in LA summers)</li>
          <li>Fan + Peltier module are the primary failure points</li>
          <li>Peltier failure: repair vs. replace assessment needed</li>
          <li>Cuisinart, NewAir, Ivation, Kalamera common brands</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="la-block">
      <div class="la-label">&#127774; LA Climate &mdash; Wine Cooler Performance Factor</div>
      <p>Los Angeles ambient temperatures significantly affect wine cooler performance. Thermoelectric units are rated for ambient temperatures up to 75&ndash;80&deg;F &mdash; a garage or unconditioned room in the San Fernando Valley or Inland Empire can exceed that on summer days, causing the unit to appear broken when it&rsquo;s simply overwhelmed. Compressor units handle higher ambient temperatures but run harder in hot environments, shortening compressor lifespan. We always assess the installation environment as part of diagnosis &mdash; sometimes the fix is relocating the unit, not replacing a part.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

